benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoicePayments/{paymentId}/customFields - Remove custom fields from payment

covered: DELETE Method - Valid Deletion: TC01, TC02, TC04, TC03, TC06, TC07, TC15, TC20, TC23 cover removal of all fields, specific fields, and edge cases (no fields, large payloads, and regression/backward compatibility).
Query Parameter Handling: TC02, TC05, TC06, TC07, TC13, TC16, TC18 cover multiple values, extraneous parameters, and invalid formats for customField inputs.
Authorization and Header Validation: TC11, TC12, TC17 cover missing header, invalid token, and header value safety checks.

Error Handling and Status Codes Coverage: scenarios include 204 (success), 400 (invalid input), 404 (not found), 401 (unauthorized), and 503 (service unavailability) across various cases (e.g., TC08, TC09, TC10, TC14, TC17, TC18, TC22).
Audit and Dependency Integration: TC21 and TC22 validate integration with dependent services (audit log) and its availability.
gaps: Concurrency / Race Conditions: No explicit concurrency race-condition test for DELETE operations.
Soft Deletes: No explicit soft-delete semantics tested (e.g., a persisted deletion flag).
403 Forbidden scenarios: Only 401/400 coverage is present; no explicit 403 case for insufficient privileges.
Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting or throttling under load.
Caching Headers: No tests for caching headers (e.g., ETag, Cache-Control) related to DELETE responses.
Internal Server Error (500): No explicit 500 scenario; only 503 service unavailability is covered.
recommendations: Add explicit concurrency/race-condition tests to verify idempotency under concurrent DELETE requests.
Add tests for soft-delete semantics and any deletion flags if applicable.
Introduce 403 Forbidden scenarios to cover insufficient privileges beyond authentication.
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to assess resilience under high request volume.
Include tests for caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) on DELETE responses if supported by the API.
Add tests simulating 500 Internal Server Error (e.g., DB failure) to ensure proper 500 handling.
